//         original_desc: "<title level=\"1\" right=\"Action\">[Create a Diversion](/Actions.aspx?ID=2387) <actions string=\"Single Action\" /></title>\r\n\r\n<traits>\r\n<trait label=\"Mental\" url=\"/Traits.aspx?ID=106\" />\r\n</traits>\r\n\r\n<column gap=\"tiny\">\r\n\r\n**Source** [Player Core](/Sources.aspx?ID=216) pg. 237 <sup>2.0</sup>\n\n</column>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nWith a gesture, a trick, or some distracting words, you can create a diversion that draws creatures' attention elsewhere. If you use a gesture or trick, this action gains the [manipulate](/Traits.aspx?ID=104) trait. If you use distracting words, it gains the [auditory](/Traits.aspx?ID=16) and [linguistic](/Traits.aspx?ID=101) traits.\n\n Attempt a single [Deception](/Skills.aspx?ID=5) check and compare it to the Perception DCs of the creatures whose attention you're trying to divert. Whether or not you succeed, creatures you attempt to divert gain a +4 circumstance bonus to their Perception DCs against your attempts to Create a Diversion for 1 minute.\r\n\r\n**Success** You become [hidden](/Conditions.aspx?ID=22) to each creature whose Perception DC is less than or equal to your result. (The hidden condition allows you to [Sneak](/Actions.aspx?ID=63) away) This lasts until the end of your turn or until you do anything except Step or use the [Stealth](/Skills.aspx?ID=15) skill to [Hide](/Actions.aspx?ID=62) or Sneak. If you Strike a creature, the creature remains [off-guard](/Conditions.aspx?ID=58) against that attack, and you then become [observed](/Conditions.aspx?ID=27). If you do anything else, you become observed just before you act unless the GM determines otherwise.<br />\r\n**Failure** You don't divert the attention of any creatures whose Perception DC exceeds your result, and those creatures are aware you were trying to trick them.",
