//         original_desc: "<title level=\"1\" right=\"Action\">[Disable a Device](/Actions.aspx?ID=2411) <actions string=\"Two Actions\" /></title>\r\n\r\n<traits>\r\n<trait label=\"Manipulate\" url=\"/Traits.aspx?ID=104\" />\r\n</traits>\r\n\r\n<column gap=\"tiny\">\r\n\r\n**Source** [Player Core](/Sources.aspx?ID=216) pg. 247 <sup>2.0</sup>\n\n</column>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThis action allows you to disarm a trap or another complex device. Often, a device requires numerous successes before becoming disabled, depending on its construction and complexity. A [thieves' toolkit](/Equipment.aspx?ID=2758) is helpful and sometimes even required to Disable a Device, as determined by the GM, and sometimes a device requires a higher proficiency rank in [Thievery](/Skills.aspx?ID=17) to disable it.\n\n Your Thievery check result determines your progress.\r\n\r\n**Critical Success** You disable the device, or you achieve two successes toward disabling a device requiring more than one success. You leave no trace of your tampering, and you can rearm the device later, if that type of device can be rearmed.<br />\r\n**Success** You disable the device, or you achieve one success toward disabling a device that requires more than one success.<br />\r\n**Critical Failure** You trigger the device.",
