//         original_desc: "<title level=\"1\" right=\"Action\">[Badger Rage](/Actions.aspx?ID=2273) <actions string=\"Single Action\" /></title>\r\n\r\n<traits>\r\n<trait label=\"Concentrate\" url=\"/Traits.aspx?ID=32\" />\r\n<trait label=\"Emotion\" url=\"/Traits.aspx?ID=60\" />\r\n<trait label=\"Mental\" url=\"/Traits.aspx?ID=106\" />\r\n</traits>\r\n\r\n<column gap=\"tiny\">\r\n\r\n**Source** [Player Core](/Sources.aspx?ID=216) pg. 207 <sup>2.0</sup>\n\n**Requirements** The badger isn’t [fatigued](/Conditions.aspx?ID=15) or raging.\r\n\r\n</column>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThe badger enters a state of pure rage that lasts for 1 minute, until there are no enemies it can perceive, or until it falls [unconscious](/Conditions.aspx?ID=38), whichever comes first. It can't voluntarily stop raging. While raging, the badger is affected in the following ways. \n<ul><li>It deals 4 additional damage with its bite attacks and 2 additional damage with its claw attacks.</li><li>It takes a –1 penalty to AC.</li><li>It can't use actions that have the [concentrate](/Traits.aspx?ID=32) trait. The animal companion can [Seek](/Actions.aspx?ID=84) even while raging.</li></ul>After it has stopped raging, it can't use Badger Rage again for 1 minute.",
