//         original_desc: "<title level=\"1\" right=\"Action\">[Tumble Through](/Actions.aspx?ID=2370) <actions string=\"Single Action\" /></title>\r\n\r\n<traits>\r\n<trait label=\"Move\" url=\"/Traits.aspx?ID=114\" />\r\n</traits>\r\n\r\n<column gap=\"tiny\">\r\n\r\n**Source** [Player Core](/Sources.aspx?ID=216) pg. 233 <sup>2.0</sup>\n\n</column>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nYou Stride up to your Speed. During this movement, you can try to move through the space of one enemy. Attempt an [Acrobatics](/Skills.aspx?ID=1) check against the enemy's Reflex DC as soon as you try to enter its space. You can Tumble Through using [Climb](/Actions.aspx?ID=33), [Fly](/Actions.aspx?ID=94), [Swim](/Actions.aspx?ID=39), or another action instead of Stride in the appropriate environment.\r\n\r\n**Success** You move through the enemy's space, treating the squares in its space as difficult terrain (every 5 feet costs 10 feet of movement). If you don't have enough Speed to move all the way through its space, you get the same effect as a failure.<br />\r\n**Failure** Your movement ends, and you trigger reactions as if you had moved out of the square you started in.",
