//         original_desc: "<title level=\"1\" right=\"Action\">[Borrow an Arcane Spell](/Actions.aspx?ID=2373) <actions string=\"\" /></title>\r\n\r\n<traits>\r\n<trait label=\"Concentrate\" url=\"/Traits.aspx?ID=32\" />\r\n<trait label=\"Exploration\" url=\"/Traits.aspx?ID=595\" />\r\n</traits>\r\n\r\n<column gap=\"tiny\">\r\n\r\n**Source** [Player Core](/Sources.aspx?ID=216) pg. 234 <sup>2.0</sup>\n\n</column>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nIf you're an arcane spellcaster who prepares spells, you can attempt to prepare a spell from someone else's arcane spellbook, arcane witch familiar, or the like. The GM sets the DC for the check based on the spell's rank and rarity; it's typically a bit easier than [Learning the Spell](/Actions.aspx?ID=25).\r\n\r\n**Success** You prepare the borrowed spell as part of your normal spell preparation.<br />\r\n**Failure** You fail to prepare the spell, but the spell slot remains available for you to prepare a different spell. You can't try to borrow this spell again until the next time you prepare spells.",
